# Stack Licenses

This file is written by `/sf:install` Stage 6 from the plugin registry. Each installed plugin's license is listed here so you know what you've agreed to use.

> **Skim before you ship anything as a hosted service.** Some plugins (notably ELv2-licensed ones) restrict commercial SaaS distribution. If you ever build a product on top of this stack and want to host it for paying users, re-read this file and check each ELv2 entry.

## Required plugins

_Populated by Stage 6 from the framework's pinned-version registry. Each entry follows this shape:_

- **`<plugin-name>`** (`<SPDX-license-id>`) — _one-line summary of what the license allows / forbids_ — [repo link]

## Conditional plugins

_Only listed if the friend opted in during Stage 3._

## Framework itself

_See the framework's own LICENSE file in the marketplace repo._

## How to re-generate this file

Re-running `/sf:install` Stage 6 rewrites this file from the current registry. If a plugin updates its license, run `/sf:doctor` to detect the change and `/sf:install --redo-stage 6` to refresh.
